          "title": "FACTORY",
          "summary": "Freeform Future Corp., a five-year-old startup based in Los Angeles, wants to turn entire buildings into automated 3D-printing factories. It has developed a technique that uses dozens of lasers to create rocket engine chambers or car parts from metal powder. The company estimates that this method could make metal parts 25 to 50 times faster than current methods at a fraction of the cost. It has raised $45 million so far from investors including Founders Fund, Threshold Ventures, and Valor Equity Partners.",
