          "order": 2,
          "title": "LAYOFFS BROKE BIG TECH’S ELITE COLLEGE HIRING PIPELINE [https://archive.ph/SppdP?utm_source=tldrnewsletter]",
          "summary": "Most tech interns were not worried by the rumors of hiring freezes in the summer of 2022. They were wrong and hundreds of thousands of jobs were lost over the following months. Unlike other years, many interns were not guaranteed return offers of full-time jobs prior to going back to school. Soon-to-be graduates who assumed that they would obtain employment have had to reconsider the value of these companies, their own prospects, and what they want from their careers.",
